# AMO Clean Transactions — Where We Left Off

At the START of any new session, briefly tell the user this status, then ask how they want to proceed. (Remove this rule once the work is deployed and confirmed.)

## Status as of 2026-06-12: built & verified locally, NOT yet deployed

We deepened the Clean Transactions tab to (a) include all loan/mortgage transfers
while excluding non-loan instruments (rents/leases, collateral, etc.) and (b) pull
real data from the recorded PDFs: assignor, assignee, parent/related entity,
property address, amount, and document title.

### Done (committed to working tree, not yet `git commit`ed)
- `collector/collect_live.py` — collects 3 doc types (AMO, ASSIGNMENT - ASG, ASSIGNMENT OF INTEREST - AIT); credentials via env vars; per-doc-type resume.
- `collector/extract_pdfs.py` (new) — downloads clerk PDF, OCRs (poppler + tesseract), Claude (Anthropic) extracts fields + classifies LOAN_TRANSFER / RENTS_LEASES / COLLATERAL / OTHER; caches in `pdf_extractions`.
- LLM provider is **Claude/Anthropic** (switched from OpenAI 2026-06-16). Both `extract_pdfs.py` and `enrich_entities.py` use the Anthropic Messages API; key via `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, model via `ANTHROPIC_MODEL` (default `claude-haiku-4-5`). NOTE: not yet live-tested against the API — needs a key to verify.
- `collector/normalize.py` — joins PDF data into `aom_events_clean`, applies loan-transfer-only filter, carries doc_title.
- `collector/database.py`, `run_weekly.sh` — doc_type in collection_log; weekly pipeline = collect → extract → normalize → enrich.
- `server/db.ts`, `server/routes.ts` — schema migrations + API returns new fields. `server/index.ts` — reusePort guarded to Linux.
- `client/src/pages/CleanEvents.tsx` — new Property + Amount columns, parent entities under names, doc title + PDF panel in expanded row.

